HEADWORD: Redact
<hw>Re*dact"</hw> <pr>(r?*d?kt")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>redactus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>redigere</ets>; pref.
<ets>red-</ets>, <ets>re-</ets>, again, back + <ets>agere</ets> to put
in motion, to drive.]</ety> <def>To reduce to form, as literary matter;
to digest and put in shape (matter for publication); to edit.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

